.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "November 2025" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.RI [command] " " [arguments]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B simple_shell
program is a lightweight UNIX command interpreter that mimics the behavior of the standard shell (sh).
It displays a prompt, waits for user input, parses the command line, and executes the requested program.

.SH FEATURES
.TP
• Displays a prompt and waits for user input
.TP
• Executes commands from the PATH or absolute path
.TP
• Handles built-in commands:
.RS
  \- exit : terminate the shell  
  \- env : print the current environment
.RE
.TP
• Handles errors gracefully (command not found)
.TP
• Supports both interactive and non-interactive modes
.TP
• Handles End-of-File (Ctrl+D)

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Nawal Alharbi and Alanoud Alanazi as part of Holberton School’s Simple Shell project.

